n-depth account of how Buryat shamans and their notion of fortune operate as ‘strange attractors’ who propagate the ongoing process of innovation-making. With its view into this long-term ‘cursing war’ between two shamanic factions in a rural Mongolian district, and the comparative findings on cursing in rural China, this book is a needed resource for anyone with an interest in the anthropology of religion, shamanism, witchcraft and genealogical change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aBlessing and cursingzChinazInner Mongolia. 0aBlessing and cursingzMongoliazBai͡andun Sum. 0aBlessing and cursingzMongoliazBai︠a︡ndun Sum. 0aBuriatszMongoliazBai͡andun SumxReligion. 0aBuriatszMongoliazBai͡andun SumxRites and ceremonies. 0aBuriatszMongoliazBai͡andun SumxSocial life and customs. 0aBuriatszMongoliazBai︠a︡ndun SumxReligion. 0aBuriatszMongoliazBai︠a︡ndun SumxRites and ceremonies. 0aBuriatszMongoliazBai︠a︡ndun SumxSocial life and customs. 0aDivinationzChinazInner Mongolia. 0aDivinationzMongoliazBai͡andun Sum. 0aDivinationzMongoliazBai︠a︡ndun Sum. 0aShamanismzChinazInner Mongolia. 0aShamanismzMongolia. 0aSocial conflictzMongoliaxReligious aspects. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311099828340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745483640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780857454836423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780857454836/original  a978-3-11-099828-3  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHE